This paper deals with machine learning tasks involving networked data, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses optimization problems and algorithms for finding appropriate weights for networked examples, which falls under the subfield of optimization (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis and risk bounds, which are relevant to the subfield of statistics (cs.ST). The use of networked data also suggests a potential connection to graph theory and network science (cs.DS), and the application of machine learning to link prediction is relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
